message.content:
A Viburnum tinus is an evergreen shrub native to the Mediterranean region.
It can grow up to 3 meters tall with a spread of 2.5 meters.
The leaves are dark green, glossy, and leathery with a slightly serrated edge.
Clusters of pink buds develop into white or pink flowers in winter-spring.
The flowers are followed by blue-black berries that attract birds.
Viburnum tinus is commonly used as an ornamental plant in gardens, borders, and hedgerows.
It is also used in traditional medicine for its antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties.
